question_text: What's the difference between Elements and Computed tabs in Styles panel?
explanation: Elements shows applied CSS rules; Computed shows final computed values after all rules applied.

question_text: How do you inspect network requests for a specific file type?
explanation: Use filter input with file extension: .css, .js, .png or type:document,type:stylesheet

question_text: What's the purpose of the "Preserve log" checkbox in Network panel?
explanation: Keeps network requests visible across page navigation for debugging multi-page flows.

question_text: How do you emulate mobile devices in DevTools?
explanation: Click Toggle Device Toolbar or Ctrl+Shift+M, select device preset or set custom dimensions.

question_text: What's the difference between localStorage and sessionStorage in Application panel?
explanation: localStorage persists across sessions; sessionStorage clears when tab closes.

question_text: How do you use breakpoints in the Sources panel for JavaScript debugging?
explanation: Click line numbers in Sources panel or right-click > Add breakpoint; use debug controls to step.

question_text: What's the purpose of the "Inspect" tool in Elements panel?
explanation: Click Inspect icon or Ctrl+Shift+C to select page elements and view their HTML/CSS.

question_text: How do you edit HTML elements live in the Elements panel?
explanation: Double-click HTML text or right-click > Edit as HTML to modify elements directly.

question_text: What's the difference between Network and Performance panels?
explanation: Network shows resource loading; Performance shows runtime metrics like CPU, rendering.

question_text: How do you clear browser cache and cookies from DevTools?
explanation: Right-click on refresh button > Empty cache and hard reload, or Application > Clear storage.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console Filter for log levels?
explanation: Filters console messages by level: Verbose, Info, Warnings, Errors for focused debugging.

question_text: How do you test responsive designs at different viewport sizes?
explanation: Use Device Toolbar to enter custom dimensions or drag edges to resize viewport.

question_text: What's the difference between CSS panel's :hov and .cls buttons?
explanation: :hov toggles pseudo-classes (hover, focus); .cls adds/removes CSS classes.

question_text: How do you copy an element's CSS styles to clipboard?
explanation: Right-click element > Copy > Copy styles or Copy selector in Styles panel.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Network Conditions tab?
explanation: Allows throttling network speed and changing user agent for testing different conditions.

question_text: How do you use console.table() for array/object display?
explanation: console.table(data) displays arrays/objects as interactive tables in console.

question_text: What's the difference between Sources and Console panels?
explanation: Sources shows source files; Console executes JavaScript and shows logs - different purposes.

question_text: How do you force element state (hover
explanation: A,Use :hov button in Styles panel or right-click element > Force state > :hover/:focus.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Coverage tab in DevTools?
explanation: Shows how much CSS/JS code is actually used vs unused for optimization.

question_text: How do you search within source files in DevTools?
explanation: Ctrl+Shift+F opens global search across all source files; Ctrl+F searches within current file.

question_text: What's the difference between XHR and Fetch in Network panel?
explanation: XHR shows XMLHttpRequest calls; Fetch shows fetch() API calls.

question_text: How do you disable JavaScript for a page in DevTools?
explanation: Settings > Preferences > Disable JavaScript or Command Menu > Disable JavaScript.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Animations panel?
explanation: Inspects and debugs CSS animations, shows timeline, and allows playback control.

question_text: How do you test page performance with Lighthouse?
explanation: Open Lighthouse panel, select categories, and generate report for performance analysis.

question_text: What's the difference between Application and Storage panels?
explanation: Application shows all web APIs; Storage focuses on storage types - Application is more comprehensive.

question_text: How do you use color picker in Styles panel?
explanation: Click color square next to color values to open picker, sample colors from page, convert formats.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Changes tab in DevTools?
explanation: Tracks CSS/JS changes made during session for review and reversion.

question_text: How do you filter console output by text or regex?
explanation: Type in filter box above console; use /regex/ for regex filtering.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Headers and Response tabs?
explanation: Headers shows HTTP headers; Response shows response body content.

question_text: How do you test print styles in DevTools?
explanation: Open Command Menu > Show Rendering, select print" media type or use Ctrl+P preview."

question_text: What's the purpose of the Sensors tab in DevTools?
explanation: Simulates device sensors like location, orientation, touch for mobile testing.

question_text: How do you use console.group() for organized logging?
explanation: console.group() starts group; console.groupEnd() ends it; creates collapsible log sections.

question_text: What's the difference between Cookies and Local Storage in Application panel?
explanation: Cookies are server-readable; Local Storage is JavaScript-only storage - different use cases.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS box model in Elements panel?
explanation: Click Box Model diagram in Computed panel or hover over padding/margin in Styles.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Performance Monitor panel?
explanation: Shows real-time CPU, JS heap, DOM nodes, event listeners for live performance monitoring.

question_text: How do you test different network speeds in DevTools?
explanation: Network panel > Throttle dropdown or Performance panel > Capture settings.

question_text: What's the difference between Event Listener and DOM Breakpoints?
explanation: Event breakpoints pause on events; DOM breakpoints pause on DOM modifications.

question_text: How do you edit and save CSS changes permanently in DevTools?
explanation: Use Workspaces to map network resources to local files or Local Overrides for persistent changes.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console Settings gear icon?
explanation: Opens Console settings for preferences like timestamps, log preservation, filter settings.

question_text: How do you inspect iframes in DevTools?
explanation: Use top dropdown in Elements panel or Console to select iframe context.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Size and Content Size?
explanation: Size shows transferred bytes; Content Size shows actual resource size.

question_text: How do you use the Command Menu in DevTools?
explanation: Ctrl+Shift+P or Cmd+Shift+P opens Command Menu to run any DevTools command quickly.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Rendering tab in DevTools?
explanation: Enables visual debugging tools like paint flashing, layer borders, FPS meter.

question_text: How do you test dark mode in DevTools?
explanation: Rendering panel > Emulate CSS media feature prefers-color-scheme: dark.

question_text: What's the difference between console.dir() and console.log()?
explanation: console.dir() shows interactive object properties; console.log() shows string representation.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS flexbox layouts in DevTools?
explanation: Elements panel shows flexbox icon; click to overlay flex lines and inspect properties.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Application panel's Service Workers tab?
explanation: Shows registered service workers, allows update, bypass, and cache inspection.

question_text: How do you search for elements by CSS selector in Elements panel?
explanation: Ctrl+F in Elements panel, type CSS selector to find matching elements.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Initiator and Priority?
explanation: Initiator shows what triggered request; Priority shows browser loading priority.

question_text: How do you use console.time() and console.timeEnd() for performance?
explanation: console.time('label') starts timer; console.timeEnd('label') stops and logs duration.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Memory panel in DevTools?
explanation: Analyzes memory usage, takes heap snapshots, detects memory leaks.

question_text: How do you test touch events in desktop DevTools?
explanation: Device Toolbar > Touch icon or Sensors panel > Emulate touch screen.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Preview and Response?
explanation: Preview shows formatted response (JSON, HTML); Response shows raw text.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS grid layouts in DevTools?
explanation: Elements panel shows grid icon; click to overlay grid lines and inspect properties.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's clear() method?
explanation: console.clear() or Ctrl+L clears console output for fresh debugging session.

question_text: How do you test different user agents in DevTools?
explanation: Network Conditions panel or Device Toolbar > Edit > Custom > User agent.

question_text: What's the difference between Application and Sources for debugging?
explanation: Application manages web APIs; Sources debugs JavaScript code - different debugging aspects.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for basic page load analysis?
explanation: Click Record in Performance panel, interact with page, stop to analyze loading timeline.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Elements panel's Accessibility tab?
explanation: Shows accessibility properties, ARIA attributes, contrast ratios for a11y testing.

question_text: How do you test WebSocket connections in DevTools?
explanation: Network panel > WS filter shows WebSocket connections and messages.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Timeline and Waterfall?
explanation: Timeline shows requests over time; Waterfall shows sequential loading - different visualizations.

question_text: How do you use console.assert() for conditional logging?
explanation: console.assert(condition, message) logs error only if condition is false.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Application panel's Cache Storage tab?
explanation: Shows cached resources by service workers for offline functionality.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS transforms and transitions in DevTools?
explanation: Use Styles panel for transform properties and Animations panel for transitions.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Domain and Remote IP?
explanation: Domain shows requested domain name; Remote IP shows resolved server IP address.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for JavaScript profiling?
explanation: Record performance, then view Call Tree or Bottom-Up to identify slow functions.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's $ and $$ shortcuts?
explanation: $ is document.querySelector; $$ is document.querySelectorAll - quick DOM access.

question_text: How do you test different pixel ratios in DevTools?
explanation: Device Toolbar > Edit > Device pixel ratio or Settings > Experiments > Device pixel ratio.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Latency and Duration?
explanation: Latency is time to first byte; Duration is total request time.

question_text: How do you inspect event listeners on elements in DevTools?
explanation: Elements panel > Event Listeners tab or Console: getEventListeners(element)

question_text: What's the purpose of the Sources panel's Snippets tab?
explanation: Create and save JavaScript snippets for repeated execution across sessions.

question_text: How do you test CSS media queries in DevTools?
explanation: Elements panel shows media query bar; click to see active queries and jump to sizes.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Cookies and Headers?
explanation: Cookies shows cookie data; Headers shows all HTTP headers.

question_text: How do you use console.count() for counting function calls?
explanation: console.count('label') increments and logs count each time it's called with same label.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Application panel's IndexedDB tab?
explanation: Shows IndexedDB databases, object stores, and data for client-side storage debugging.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS custom properties (variables) in DevTools?
explanation: Computed panel shows custom properties or filter by "--" in Styles panel.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Blocked and Stalled?
explanation: Blocked shows waiting for priority; Stalled shows TCP connection issues.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for memory usage analysis?
explanation: Record performance with Memory checkbox enabled to see memory usage over time.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's copy() function?
explanation: copy(object) copies string representation to clipboard for sharing.

question_text: How do you test CSS backdrop-filter in DevTools?
explanation: Use Styles panel to edit backdrop-filter property and see real-time visual changes.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Size and Decoded Size?
explanation: Size shows transferred bytes; Decoded Size shows size after decompression.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for paint flashing visualization?
explanation: Enable "Paint flashing" in Rendering panel during performance recording.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Elements panel's Properties tab?
explanation: Shows DOM properties and prototype chain of selected element.

question_text: How do you test CSS scroll-behavior in DevTools?
explanation: Edit scroll-behavior property in Styles panel and test scrolling on page.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Type and Initiator?
explanation: Type shows resource type (document, script); Initiator shows what triggered request.

question_text: How do you use console.trace() for stack trace debugging?
explanation: console.trace() prints stack trace showing function call hierarchy.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Application panel's Background Services tab?
explanation: Shows background service workers, push notifications, background sync for PWA testing.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS position properties in DevTools?
explanation: Use Styles panel to edit position property and see visual changes in real-time.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Schema and Domain?
explanation: Schema shows protocol (http/https); Domain shows server domain.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for layout shift debugging?
explanation: Record performance and look for Layout Shift events to identify shifting elements.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's monitor() function?
explanation: monitor(function) logs function calls with arguments and return values.

question_text: How do you test CSS filter effects in DevTools?
explanation: Edit filter property in Styles panel to apply and test blur, brightness, contrast effects.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Started and Time?
explanation: Started shows absolute start time; Time shows duration from start to finish.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for first contentful paint (FCP) analysis?
explanation: Record performance and look for first paint event to identify FCP timing.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Elements panel's Layout panel?
explanation: Shows layout tools for Grid, Flexbox, and overlays for alignment debugging.

question_text: How do you test CSS mix-blend-mode in DevTools?
explanation: Edit mix-blend-mode property in Styles panel to test different blending effects.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Method and Status?
explanation: Method shows HTTP method (GET, POST); Status shows response code (200, 404).

question_text: How do you use console.profile() for JavaScript profiling?
explanation: console.profile('label') starts profiler; console.profileEnd('label') stops it.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Application panel's Web SQL tab?
explanation: Shows Web SQL databases (deprecated) for legacy web app debugging.

question_text: How do you inspect CSS text properties in DevTools?
explanation: Use Styles panel to edit font-family, size, spacing, and other text properties.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Headers and Cookies?
explanation: Headers shows all HTTP headers; Cookies shows only cookie-related headers.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for interaction timing analysis?
explanation: Record performance during user interactions to measure event handling and response times.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's debug() function?
explanation: console.debug() logs debug messages (visible when Verbose level enabled).

question_text: How do you test CSS will-change property in DevTools?
explanation: Edit will-change property in Styles panel to test performance optimization hints.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Transferred and Size?
explanation: Transferred shows actual bytes sent; Size shows resource size (may be compressed).

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for main thread activity analysis?
explanation: Record performance and analyze Main section to see JavaScript execution and rendering.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Elements panel's Event Listeners pane?
explanation: Shows all event listeners attached to selected element for debugging event handling.

question_text: How do you test CSS clip-path in DevTools?
explanation: Edit clip-path property in Styles panel to create and test different shape clippings.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Connection ID and Request ID?
explanation: Connection ID identifies TCP connection; Request ID identifies individual request.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for rendering pipeline analysis?
explanation: Record performance and analyze Painting, Compositing, and GPU sections.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's table() with column filtering?
explanation: console.table(data, columns) shows table with only specified columns for focused viewing.

question_text: How do you test CSS aspect-ratio in DevTools?
explanation: Edit aspect-ratio property in Styles panel to test different aspect ratio constraints.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's From Cache and From Memory Cache?

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for JavaScript heap analysis?
explanation: Record performance with Memory checkbox to see heap size and garbage collection.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's groupCollapsed() function?

question_text: How do you test CSS object-fit in DevTools?
explanation: Edit object-fit property in Styles panel to test different image fitting options.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Request and Response headers?
explanation: Request headers sent to server; Response headers received from server.

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for long task analysis?

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's timeStamp() function?

question_text: How do you test CSS gap property in DevTools?

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's Queued and Started?

question_text: How do you use the Performance panel for frame rate analysis?
explanation: Record performance and check FPS chart to identify dropped frames and animation issues.

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's countReset() function?

question_text: How do you test CSS writing-mode in DevTools?
explanation: Edit writing-mode property in Styles panel to test horizontal/vertical text direction.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's First Byte and Content Download?

question_text: What's the purpose of the Console's dirxml() function?

question_text: How do you test CSS scroll-snap in DevTools?

question_text: How do you test CSS content-visibility in DevTools?
explanation: Edit content-visibility property in Styles panel to test rendering optimization.

question_text: What's the difference between Network panel's SSL and TCP Handshake?

question_text: How do you use DOM breakpoints to debug JavaScript modifications?

explanation: XHR breakpoints pause on AJAX requests; Event breakpoints pause on DOM events.
